article.headline: Northwestern St. 82, Lamar 79
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Devon Baker and Will Pratt scored 19 points each as Northwestern State defeated Lamar 82-79 on Saturday. The victory was the third straight for the Demons (10-15, 5-7, Southland Conference), who have scored 82 points in each of them. Justin Nabors scored 26 points, 21 in the first half, and grabbed 14 rebounds for the Cardinals (14-14, 5-7), whose last lead, 29-27, came 8:09 before halftime. The Demons then went on an 18-4 run, including 10 points by Baker, to lead 45-33 with 1:22 left in the half. Northwestern State led throughout the second half. Lamar got within three, 79-76, on Reggie Mathis' 3-pointer with 23 seconds left, but Baker made one of two free throws with 19 seconds left and sank two at the 0:07 mark. Damon Jones added 14 points and Pratt had a career-high 11 rebounds for the Demons. Anthony Miles scored 16 points and Mathis 15 for Lamar.
